    "title": "Add ability to easily read the Bitcoin whitepaper from the GUI",
    "body": "The bitcoin whitepaper was removed recently from a prominent bitcoin website in response to a legal challenge from an idiot/scammer. Luckily, the whitepaper is embedded in the a transaction and can be read [with a little programming](https://bitcoin.stackexchange.com/questions/35959/how-is-the-whitepaper-decoded-from-the-blockchain-tx-with-1000x-m-of-n-multisi/35970#35970).\r\n\r\nI'd like to be able to click a button (perhaps in the menu bar?) in the GUI that will automatically decode the whitepaper transaction and open the PDF in my default PDF reader.\r\n\r\nI've considered doing a search for \"Bitcoin Whitepaper\" but I believe that is bad OpSec.\r\n\r\n\r\n",
